SUMMARY:Queer Voices in Print
LOCATION:1426 Beaudry (métro Beaudry)
DESCRIPTION:2026-03-07 17:00:00\n\n1426 Beaudry (métro Beaudry)\n\nhttps:
 //www.openstreetmap.org/node/4852683788\n\nPoets\, writers\, and publisher
 s Faith Paré\, Chris DiRaddo (@violet_hour_mtl )\, and Eli Tareq El Beche
 lany-Lynch (@metonymypress ) discuss independent queer publishing as a for
 m of community archiving. How do book clubs\, small presses\, and poetry r
 eadings document queer lives and preserve stories that mainstream publishi
 ng overlooks?\nThe conversation will explore creating spaces for queer ang
 lophone voices in Montreal\, navigating the city’s language divide\, fin
 ding and prioritizing emerging writers\, and what it means to put these st
 ories in print and circulate them as acts of cultural preservation.\nThe p
 anel will be followed by a poetry reading from local queer poets Eli Tareq
  El Bechelany-Lynch (@sherlockh0m0)\, Liana Cusmano (@lucadove6 )\, Erin M
 ouré (@vagaceira )\, Faith Paré (@paretriarchy )\, and Misha Solomon (@m
 ishasolomon )\nL’Euguélionne Bookstore @librairieleuguelionne\nMarch 7\
 , 5-7 pm\nPart of Owning Our Histories: Celebrating Queer &amp\; BIPOC DIY
  Archives. 10 events celebrating how communities document themselves.\nFre
 e and open to the public.\n#queermtl #diyarchives #owningourhistories #que
 erpoetry #angloquebec\n&nbsp\;
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/node/4852683788
END:VEVENT
